Subject: Re: [T2] Removing the side cover necessary to replace side window?



On Thu, 1 Aug 2002, Courtney Hook wrote:

> I'm outside looking at the rear drivers side window that some idiot smashed
> for me, and the side cover runs along just underneath it on the very edge of
> the seal. Is it necessary to remove it to replace the window?? Also, if so,
> it appears to be pretty much arc-welded on there, I got one screw out, need
> to remove the other, then what???

[...]

3 screws, front, middle, rear (at least on my '71)

Remove them and tap the cover upward with a rubber hammer.  It is a
friction fit in a groove in the body.  It might take a fair whack to get
it moving.

George Lyle

